-- Electricity Cut to 60,000 Homes as Storms Hit South Australia, ABC Says
-- Robert Fenner
-- 2010-07-10T00:15:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-10/electricity-cut-to-60-000-homes-as-storms-hit-south-australia-abc-says.html

          
          
             About 60,000 homes in South
Australia state lost electricity as storms blocked roads and
damaged powerlines, the Australian Broadcasting Corp. reported
on its website. The blackouts affected the state capital
Adelaide and regional areas, the ABC said, citing local
emergency services.  
